MEC for education, Bonakele Majuba, encouraged learners at Lowveld High School to work hard  in their grade 12 National Senior Certificate examination. This was during his visit on Thursday. WATCH:  ALSO WATCH: R37 roadblock outside Mbombela cleared Majuba wished the learners good luck. “Good luck always goes with hard work,” he said. There was a press conference at the school on the state of readiness for the management of the grade 12 National Senior Certificate examination.